03:22.408 --> 03:24.309
Your Annes, yes. Your Annes.

03:24.343 --> 03:26.074
Well... Two of them, at least.

03:26.179 --> 03:30.632
This titan of the stage
played Anne from 1965 to 1980.

03:30.667 --> 03:33.952
And... Linda over here
is our current Anne.

03:33.986 --> 03:36.154
You direct the local <i>Anne
Of Green Gables</i> play?

03:36.188 --> 03:38.823
Indeed. My Annes and I
have been watching you

03:38.857 --> 03:41.693
ever since you arrived in town.
In fact...

03:41.727 --> 03:44.829
many of us are watching you still.

03:44.863 --> 03:48.232
(eerie music)

03:51.698 --> 03:53.180
- Oh, my goodness!
- Woah, woah, woah!

03:53.206 --> 03:56.507
Oh! Yeah. Alright.

03:56.542 --> 03:58.910
Simply put, Cavendish is the home

03:58.944 --> 04:01.146
of Anne Of Green Gables and it is...

04:01.180 --> 04:04.916
