you're convinced it's real,

12:20.352 --> 12:22.386
why would you still come here?

12:23.383 --> 12:26.223
I really want to be an actor.

12:27.319 --> 12:28.158
Holy hell!

12:28.193 --> 12:30.194
That's the most pathetic thing
I've ever heard in my life.

12:30.228 --> 12:32.062
Why isn't he Creepy Ted?

12:34.266 --> 12:36.333
(insects chirping)

12:36.368 --> 12:38.736
(Andy): Idea for an article.
"Isolation."

12:38.770 --> 12:42.006
"Boredom." We are currently in an old...

12:42.040 --> 12:45.175
I want to say... Georgian house.

12:45.210 --> 12:47.177
It is the middle of nowhere.

12:48.401 --> 12:51.181
My feelings so far:

12:51.216 --> 12:53.117
nervousness...

12:53.151 --> 12:56.453
and a penetrating dread...

12:57.102 --> 13:00.724
plus some hunger that was staved off
because Mark thought to bring peaches.

13:05.075 --> 13:07.298
(whispering):
My sisters and I want your seed.

13:07.332 --> 13:09.466
(moaning)

13:09.501 --> 13:11.802
(soft chuckle) Oh, my God!

13:11.836 --> 13:13.804
Oh, Andy! Look!

13:13.838 --> 13:15.940
Look what's happening to
the crotch of his pants.

13:15.974 --> 13:17.292
I know what you want me
to look at, Mark,

13:17.309 --> 13:20.411
- and I am not looking.
- (knocking)

13:21.757 --> 13:23.981
Gentlemen, it's time.

13:25.031 --> 13:26.850
Oh no!

13:29.458 --> 13:32.489
Please, gentlemen,
come join us in the circle.

13:33.274 --> 13:34.791
Anne... Hello, Anne.

13:35.695 --> 13:37.428
Hi. Hello, everyone.

13:37.462 --> 13:40.998
- Nice to see you all again.
- Here in the presence

13:41.032 --> 13:44.935
of Vivian, the oldest living Anne,

13:45.737 --> 13:48.839
and in the name of Lucy Maud Montgomery,

13:48.873 --> 13:51.008
the "Creator",

13:51.042 --> 13:53.010
from whose pen sprung a world,

13:54.037 --> 13:55.946
we move into this new year

13:56.748 --> 13:59.783
with a ritual that we do every year:

14:00.796 --> 14:04.655
the twisting of the tongues.

14:07.206 --> 14:12.162
- Unique New York.
- (all): Unique New York.

14:12.197 --> 14:14.965
P-E-I, pizza pie.

14:15.000 --> 14:17.101
(all): P-E-I, pizza pie.

14:17.135 --> 14:19.803
And Anne had a plan

14:19.838 --> 14:22.640
to flummox the man!

14:22.674 --> 14:24.975
(all): Anne had a plan

14:25.010 --> 14:27.311
to flummox the man!

14:27.345 --> 14:31.382
- Inhale, Anne!
- (all inhaling)

14:31.416 --> 14:36.320
(vocalizing): A-a-a-a-anne.

14:36.354 --> 14:40.624
(all): A-a-a-a-a-anne.

14:40.659 --> 14:45.129
Anne, be honest. Do you ever think
about leaving Green Gables?

14:45.163 --> 14:47.498
Oh, I don't know, Gilbert.

14:47.532 --> 14:49.800
I maybe had a thought
like that once. But then,

14:49.834 --> 14:51.935
I looked around at all the green,

14:52.706 --> 14:54.338
all the gables

14:55.014 --> 14:57.041
and I remembered.

14:57.075 --> 15:00.344
This is home.

15:02.964 --> 15:05.338
Andy! Andy!

15:12.991 --> 15:14.825
Why don't you two kiss so I can watch?

15:14.859 --> 15:18.462
- (gasps)
- Get out of here, Creepy Ted!

15:18.496 --> 15:20.831
Can't you see we don't want you?

15:20.865 --> 15:22.866
Why don't you make me, Gilbert?

15:23.997 --> 15:26.070
- Mayhaps I shall!
- Hey!

15:26.104 --> 15:27.738
No, no, this is good.
Use the fear, use the fear.

15:27.772 --> 15:30.107
Clearly, Gilbert is a
stronger man than you but you,

15:30.141 --> 15:33.243
you're a proud old creep, aren't you?
Aren't you, Ted?

15:33.278 --> 15:35.312
That's right, you proud old creep!

15:35.346 --> 15:37.681
- Fight me, you old bastard!
- It's not in the script.

15:37.716 --> 15:39.550
Forget the script! Use the moment!

15:39.584 --> 15:42.653
Come at me, Creepy Ted, you old bastard!
Poor, old bastard!

15:42.687 --> 15:44.822
OK! Alright! Uh... Screw you, Gilbert!

15:44.856 --> 15:46.924
Anne deserves better than you!

15:46.958 --> 15:49.893
Better than me?
Like who, Creepy Ted? Like you?

15:49.928 --> 15:52.262
- Yes! Yes, like me!
- With your receding hairline

15:52.297 --> 15:55.101
and your litany of
magazine rejection letters?

15:55.167 --> 15:58.068
- Hey!
- Oh, he doesn't like that!

15:58.103 --> 16:00.170
Creepy Ted doesn't like it!

16:00.205 --> 16:02.106
No, Creepy Ted doesn't like that!

16:02.140 --> 16:04.875
Well, come at me, Creepy Ted!
Show me what you got!

16:04.909 --> 16:08.779
- Motherf...!
- Oh, yeah! Yeah!

16:08.813 --> 16:10.948
(screaming)

16:10.982 --> 16:13.450
Get off of me! (muffled speech)

16:13.485 --> 16:15.452
Get off of me!

16:15.487 --> 16:17.287
- (angry shout)
- (gasps)

16:19.173 --> 16:20.057
How was that?

16:20.091 --> 16:22.493
That felt really good.

16:25.531 --> 16:26.563
What's this?

16:26.598 --> 16:29.466
Oh, sorry. I'm just using it
to take some notes.

16:29.501 --> 16:32.803
Notes. You are...

16:34.255 --> 16:37.141
- You're a spy?
- What? No! I'm a writer.

16:37.175 --> 16:39.243
What rival theatre company
are you writing for?

16:39.277 --> 16:43.680
The Eastern Front?
Charlottetown Players?

16:43.715 --> 16:46.083
Uh... It's just
for a magazine article or...

16:46.117 --> 16:48.018
- LIAR!
- Woah! Woah! Woah! OK!

16:48.052 --> 16:51.088
OK! OK! Ladies,
I feel like there's been some sort

16:51.122 --> 16:53.590
of a misunderstanding here.
Andy's not a spy

16:53.625 --> 16:56.260
or anything interesting like that.
He's just a very boring writer

16:56.294 --> 16:58.762
who documents the history
of potatoes, for instance.

16:58.797 --> 17:00.931
And I'm also writing a
semi-autobiographical novel.

17:00.965 --> 17:02.933
Like I said, very boring.

17:02.967 --> 17:05.102
- Holy moly!
- It's my member you want.

17:05.136 --> 17:07.137
- My member!
- OK, Travis,

17:07.172 --> 17:09.205
I feel like you're misreading
this situation, pal.

17:09.240 --> 17:11.541
- (shrieking)
- Maybe not! Maybe not! OK!

17:11.576 --> 17:13.777
I think Travis wanted that to happen!

17:13.811 --> 17:15.779
- Oh! Jesus...
- OK! Let's go! Go, go!

17:15.814 --> 17:17.948
- Go, go, go!
- Come one! Come on!

17:17.982 --> 17:20.284
- Lock the door!
- OK! OK!

17:20.318 --> 17:22.452
- (murmuring)
- (shushing)

17:22.487 --> 17:24.454
Do you think they heard us come down?

17:24.489 --> 17:26.790
- I don't think so.
- This is it. This is how I die.

17:26.825 --> 17:28.792
Yeah. Alone in a backwoods
farmhouse murdered

17:28.827 --> 17:30.994
- by a bunch of Anne Shirleys.
- Who the hell is Shirley?

17:31.029 --> 17:33.497
That's Anne's last name.
You still haven't read the book?

17:33.531 --> 17:35.499
- When would I have read the book?
- I don't know!

17:35.533 --> 17:38.153
- Browse a Wikipedia article!
- (shushing)

17:38.188 --> 17:40.604
It's gonna be fine.
They don't know where we are.

17:40.638 --> 17:43.640
Let's just wait till they go to bed
and then sneak out the back.

17:43.675 --> 17:47.316
- (banging)
- OK. They might know where we are.

17:51.418 --> 17:53.986
Uh... Give yourself
over to the universe!

17:54.020 --> 17:56.789
What happens when your life is a toilet
and the universe takes a big old dump?

17:56.823 --> 17:59.491
Oh, that's good. You should
write that one down, actually.

17:59.526 --> 18:01.627
Travis was right, Mark.
We are going to die here.

18:01.661 --> 18:03.662
No, Andy, Travis was wrong

18:03.697 --> 18:06.165
in every respect.
And I'm not dying tonight.

18:07.181 --> 18:08.968
I can promise you that.

18:09.571 --> 18:11.303
- Storm doors!
- Are there storm doors?

18:11.338 --> 18:14.273
- There are storm doors.
- Oh, thank God! I was not ready to use this. Let's go!

18:14.307 --> 18:16.775
- (grunting)
- Oh, God...

18:16.810 --> 18:18.877
- Aaaah!
- Oh! OK...

18:18.912 --> 18:20.811
- Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait!
- (repeating): What?

18:21.131 --> 18:23.716
The car keys are in the house!
Yes, the car keys are in the house!

18:23.750 --> 18:25.617
- I got this.
- What are you doing?

18:25.652 --> 18:27.419
(grunting)

18:27.454 --> 18:31.023
What are you doing? Stop it!
Stop it! Stop it! Stop it!

18:31.057 --> 18:32.435
I'm gonna break it so we can
get in and we can drive away!

18:32.459 --> 18:35.916
I can't drive the car, OK?
I don't have the car keys!

18:35.951 --> 18:37.329
Oh, you need them for the ignition.

18:37.364 --> 18:40.153
- Yes, I need them for the ignition, Mark!
- OK, I'm sorry, I forgot about that part.

18:40.188 --> 18:42.434
- Woah! Just hotwire it! Hotwire the car!
- Hotwire it?

18:42.469 --> 18:44.737
- I don't know how to hotwire a car! Touch the what? The wires?
- Touch the... Touch the...

18:44.771 --> 18:46.772
- The wires together. Touch the wires together!
- The wires?

18:46.806 --> 18:48.440
Like they do in the movies?
Like carjackers do in movies?

18:48.475 --> 18:50.476
- Yeah, yeah!
- That's a movie, Mark!

18:50.510 --> 18:52.083
OK, well, I don't know
what's movie and what's real!

18:52.146 --> 18:53.746
Oh, my God! Why didn't you think
before you go around

18:53.847 --> 18:56.648
- smashing things with the heel of a sword?!
- You say that like that's

18:56.683 --> 18:59.051
- a thing I do. I did that once.
- Oh, my...

18:59.085 --> 19:03.288
- Gentlemen!
- Should... sh-sh-should we run?

19:03.915 --> 19:07.393
Uh... No.

19:07.427 --> 19:09.495
- Don't worry, pal.
- What?

19:09.529 --> 19:11.530
- I got this.
- What are you doing?

19:11.564 --> 19:15.501
Annes, it's time for you to meet your...

19:15.535 --> 19:18.670
Oh, crap, it's decorative!
It's a decorative sword, Andy!

19:18.705 --> 19:21.573
- OK... Hi! Here's the thing...
- Andrew...

19:21.608 --> 19:24.043
You've broken a sacred
trust here tonight.

19:24.077 --> 19:28.347
We invited you into the fold
and you repaid us with deceit.

19:28.381 --> 19:30.682
This is your final warning:

19:31.427 --> 19:33.352
either tell us who you're working for

19:33.386 --> 19:35.421
or we will be forced...

19:38.243 --> 19:40.826
...to fire you from the play.

19:42.836 --> 19:45.230
- Is that it?
- Was that all that's gonna happen?

19:45.265 --> 19:47.866
- Creepy Ted!
- (terrified moans)

19:47.901 --> 19:49.835
Creepy Ted!

19:49.869 --> 19:52.271
- (all exclaiming)
- Vivian!

19:52.305 --> 19:57.743
I will not kiss in front of you,
you creepy horse-tugger!

19:57.777 --> 20:00.248
I was standing there, like,
what the hell is going on?

20:00.280 --> 20:03.582
And Andy starts screaming:
"I'm not Creepy Ted!"

20:03.616 --> 20:07.753
(laughing) "I'm not Creepy Ted!"

20:07.787 --> 20:10.556
"Please, I'm not Creepy Ted!"

20:10.590 --> 20:14.626
- That is so adorable!
- I'm gonna piss my pants!

20:14.661 --> 20:16.628
I'm telling you,
it's really good to laugh again.

20:16.663 --> 20:20.032
Shut up, Dr. Green.
This is why I don't open myself up

20:20.066 --> 20:22.234
to the universe!
Because nothing means anything!

20:22.268 --> 20:24.203
Travis opened himself up to the universe

20:24.237 --> 20:26.572
- and he got trampled to death!
- Well, medically speaking,

20:26.606 --> 20:29.108
that's nearly to death.
How are you doing, partner?

20:29.142 --> 20:32.711
Better. And at least, it took a
whole pack of them to take <i>me</i> down.

20:32.745 --> 20:35.581
(laughing)

20:35.615 --> 20:37.749
Hell yeah, Travis! That's my man!

20:37.784 --> 20:39.918
- You like Travis, now?
- I'm coming around to him.

20:39.953 --> 20:41.920
Oh... Anyway,
it looks like everything worked out

20:41.955 --> 20:44.089
in the end. You guys
will have to excuse me, though.

20:44.124 --> 20:46.091
I have to inform a
family that a loved one

20:46.126 --> 20:50.229
didn't make it, so... Excuse me.

20:50.263 --> 20:52.865
Hey! You guys wanna see some photos
of that old lady taking out Andy?

20:52.899 --> 20:54.800
- Yeah!
- You got photos?

20:54.834 --> 20:56.735
- Ow!
- (laughing)

20:56.769 --> 20:59.538
- That... that's it! Oh, woah!
- Come on, man!

20:59.572 --> 21:01.540
That's... That's his phone anyway.

21:01.574 --> 21:05.010
Bryn's got mine. (sighs)

21:05.044 --> 21:08.380
♪ You can make your life
a misery if you try ♪

